      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An escrow account is a neutral third-party account where funds for the home's closing remain safely until both you and the seller agree on the final details. Its primary purpose is to prevent fraud by ensuring money isn't released to the seller until the property title is officially transferred and all conditions are met. In Toronto, this service is especially critical for protecting your investment during a busy market, though you can arrange this agreement separately with the lawyer handling your closing. Don't worry, your realtor is helping you navigate a standard safety measure that protects you until the deal closes.",
